---
import Main from '../layouts/main.astro';

const sectionClass = 'sa05-section py-8';
const containerClass = 'max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6';
const slotCards = [
  { time: '10:05 – 10:55', label: 'Full hour' },
  { time: '10:05 – 10:30', label: 'First half of the hour' },
  { time: '10:35 – 11:00', label: 'Second half of the hour' },
];
---

<Main
  title="Start at :05 — Smarter meeting times | Gerrit Garbereder"
  description="Start meetings five minutes after the hour. Fewer late arrivals, calmer transitions, built-in breaks. A simple meeting policy that works."
  canonical="https://start-at-05.com/"
  keywords="meeting policy, meeting times, Start at :05, scheduling, productivity, calendar, back-to-back meetings"
  extraFontCssVariable="--font-fraunces"
>
  <div class="start-at-05 min-h-screen flex flex-col">
    <header
      role="banner"
      class="sa05-hero relative overflow-hidden px-4 py-8 sm:py-12"
    >
      <div
        class="sa05-hero-glow absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none"
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
      </div>
      <div class={`${containerClass} relative z-10`}>
        <h1 class="start-at-05-h1 font-light leading-tight tracking-tight">
          Start at <span class="sa05-accent font-normal italic">:05</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="sa05-hero-lead lead text-lg mt-8 max-w-[28ch]">
          Start meetings five minutes after the hour. Fewer late arrivals,
          calmer transitions, built-in breaks.
        </p>

        <div
          class="mt-8 py-8"
          role="img"
          aria-label="Timeline: 10:00, 10:05 start, 10:55 end, 11:00"
        >
          <ul class="timeline-vertical sm:hidden space-y-8 list-none">
            <li class="relative flex items-center min-h-[2rem]">
              <span
                class="timeline-dot timeline-dot-idle absolute w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full"
                aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="text-sm timeline-hour">10:00</span>
            </li>
            <li class="relative flex items-center min-h-[2rem]">
              <span
                class="timeline-dot timeline-dot-active absolute w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full"
                aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="timeline-label text-sm font-medium">10:05 Start</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="relative flex items-center min-h-[2rem]">
              <span
                class="timeline-dot timeline-dot-mid absolute w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full"
                aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="timeline-label text-sm font-medium">10:55 End</span>
            </li>
            <li class="relative flex items-center min-h-[2rem]">
              <span
                class="timeline-dot timeline-dot-idle absolute w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full"
                aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="text-sm timeline-hour">11:00</span>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div
            class="timeline-horizontal hidden sm:flex items-start justify-center gap-0 flex-nowrap"
          >
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-4 shrink-0">
              <span
                class="w-3.5 h-3.5 rounded-full timeline-dot-idle"
                aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="text-sm timeline-hour">10:00</span>
            </div>
            <div
              class="timeline-connector timeline-connector-idle w-6 sm:w-8 shrink-0 max-w-[40px]"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-4 shrink-0">
              <span
                class="w-3.5 h-3.5 rounded-full timeline-dot-active"
                aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="timeline-label text-sm font-medium">10:05 Start</span
              >
            </div>
            <div
              class="timeline-connector timeline-connector-active flex-1 min-w-[24px]"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-4 shrink-0">
              <span
                class="w-3.5 h-3.5 rounded-full timeline-dot-mid"
                aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="timeline-label text-sm font-medium">10:55 End</span>
            </div>
            <div
              class="timeline-connector timeline-connector-idle w-6 sm:w-8 shrink-0 max-w-[40px]"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-4 shrink-0">
              <span
                class="w-3.5 h-3.5 rounded-full timeline-dot-idle"
                aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="text-sm timeline-hour">11:00</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main id="main-content" class="sa05-main flex-1">
      <article aria-label="Start at :05 meeting policy">
        <section class={sectionClass}>
          <div class={containerClass}>
            <h2
              class="start-at-05-h2 mb-8 text-[1.875rem] font-light leading-snug"
            >
              Why not "on the hour"?
            </h2>
            <p class="lead text-lg mb-8">
              Meetings usually are about <strong class="sa05-strong">30</strong> or
              <strong class="sa05-strong">60 minutes</strong> long. Many teams use
              50‑minute slots to create buffers—but that creates friction too.
            </p>
            <div class="sa05-card card my-8 rounded-2xl p-6 text-base">
              <h3 class="start-at-05-h3 mb-8 leading-snug">
                Problems with 50‑minute blocks
              </h3>
              <ul class="list m-0 flex list-none flex-col gap-4 p-0 text-base">
                <li
                  class="sa05-list-li start-at-05-list-li flex gap-4 leading-[1.5]"
                >
                  Rooms are often booked until the full hour anyway, so you
                  can't get in early.
                </li>
                <li
                  class="sa05-list-li start-at-05-list-li flex gap-4 leading-[1.5]"
                >
                  People think in round hours. "Meeting at 10:00" means they may
                  show at 10:00—and miss a 10:00 sharp start.
                </li>
                <li
                  class="sa05-list-li start-at-05-list-li flex gap-4 leading-[1.5]"
                >
                  It's easier to stick to the full 50 minutes by starting late
                  rather than by forcing a hard stop on the hour.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class={sectionClass}>
          <div class={containerClass}>
            <h2
              class="start-at-05-h2 mb-8 text-[1.875rem] font-light leading-snug"
            >
              The fix: Start at :05
            </h2>
            <p class="text-base mb-8">
              Schedule meetings to <span class="sa05-accent font-semibold"
                >start at :05</span
              > (five minutes after the hour)—or at :35 for half-hour slots. You keep
              buffer time between back-to-backs while matching how people think about
              times: "meeting at 10" still gives a few minutes to get there, and you're
              done before the next round hour so the next meeting can start at :05
              too.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class={containerClass}>
            <div
              class="sa05-card card highlight my-8 rounded-2xl relative overflow-hidden p-6"
            >
              <h3 class="start-at-05-h3 mb-8 leading-snug">Why it works</h3>
              <ul class="list m-0 flex list-none flex-col gap-4 p-0 text-base">
                <li
                  class="sa05-list-li start-at-05-list-li flex gap-4 leading-[1.5]"
                >
                  People still think "on the hour" but you start at :05 (or
                  :35).
                </li>
                <li
                  class="sa05-list-li start-at-05-list-li flex gap-4 leading-[1.5]"
                >
                  Everyone gets at least a 5‑minute break between meetings.
                </li>
                <li
                  class="sa05-list-li start-at-05-list-li flex gap-4 leading-[1.5]"
                >
                  "Meeting at 10" still gives a 5‑minute window to reach the
                  room.
                </li>
                <li
                  class="sa05-list-li start-at-05-list-li flex gap-4 leading-[1.5]"
                >
                  Encouraged to end on time by following meetings.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class={containerClass}>
            <h3 class="start-at-05-h3 mb-4 leading-snug">Examples</h3>
            <p class="text-base mb-4">
              For <strong class="sa05-strong">60‑minute</strong> meetings, start at
              :05 and end at :55.
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 mb-8">
              <div class="sa05-slot slot rounded-xl p-6 text-center text-base">
                <div class="time font-light text-2xl mb-4">
                  {slotCards[0].time}
                </div>
                <div class="label text-sm">{slotCards[0].label}</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <p class="text-base mb-4">
              For <strong class="sa05-strong">30‑minute</strong> meetings, start at
              :05 or :35.
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2">
              {
                slotCards.slice(1).map((slot) => (
                  <div class="sa05-slot slot rounded-xl p-6 text-center text-base">
                    <div class="time font-light text-2xl mb-4">{slot.time}</div>
                    <div class="label text-sm">{slot.label}</div>
                  </div>
                ))
              }
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class={`${sectionClass} pb-8`}>
          <div class={containerClass}>
            <div
              class="sa05-card card highlight rounded-2xl relative overflow-hidden p-6"
            >
              <h2 class="start-at-05-h2 text-[1.875rem] leading-snug mb-8">
                Summary
              </h2>
              <p class="text-base mb-8">
                By consistently using <span class="sa05-accent font-semibold"
                  >Start at :05</span
                > (and :35 for half-hour slots), we:
              </p>
              <ul class="list m-0 flex list-none flex-col gap-4 p-0 text-base">
                <li
                  class="sa05-list-li start-at-05-list-li flex gap-4 leading-[1.5]"
                >
                  Reduce lateness from "on-the-hour" mental scheduling
                </li>
                <li
                  class="sa05-list-li start-at-05-list-li flex gap-4 leading-[1.5]"
                >
                  Make room transitions easier
                </li>
                <li
                  class="sa05-list-li start-at-05-list-li flex gap-4 leading-[1.5]"
                >
                  Build in short but meaningful breaks between sessions
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </article>
    </main>

    <footer
      role="contentinfo"
      class="sa05-footer pt-8 pb-8 text-center text-xs font-normal"
    >
      <div class={containerClass}>
        <p>
          Start at <span class="sa05-accent">:05</span> — Smarter meeting times
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          By <a
            href="https://www.garbereder.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            aria-label="Gerrit Garbereder (opens in new window)"
            class="rounded focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-[var(--sa05-accent)]"
            >Gerrit Garbereder</a
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </div>
</Main>
